description.narrative: (Tanzania): .The Public Sector Systems Strengthening (PS3) activity strengthens the Government of Tanzania's (GOT) ability to govern, finance, and deliver quality public services, particularly for underserved populations within Tanzania. With FY 2018 funds, U.S. government will strengthen local government authority (LGA) systems to promote inclusive and evidence-based planning, management, and implementation of public services in health, education, nutrition and local governance. The activity's major interventions will include designing and deploying financial accountability systems that ensure greater fiduciary controls and transparency across regional, district, and community governments; improving information systems to facilitate inclusive and informed annual planning processes at health and educational facilities; and enabling data-driven and need-based national and district level human resource deployment across health and education sectors. Additionally, PS3 will emphasize sustainability by providing technical assistance to the GOT to develop national guidelines, online training tools, and on-the-job training and mentoring programs for users of established GOT information systems. This activity.contributes to interventions related to Malaria, Family Planning and Reproductive.Health. While USAID funds PS3 activities in 13 regions and with 93 LGAs within Tanzania, the GOT further deploys the systems established under the activity across the rest of the country in 185 LGAs. PS3's broad implementation strategy directly supports the U.S. government's objective to improve the GOT's delivery of services, increase accountability within the GOT, and improve the health of Tanzanians. By jointly designing and deploying its interventions in collaboration with the GOT, it directly contributes to the GOTs' ability to attain self-reliance, a US Foreign Policy priority... ...
